The author, Jill, and the readers are celebrating Easter Sunday, a day of joy and hope. They reflect on Christ's Resurrection and the defeat of death through faith, hope, and love. They are grateful that many can celebrate Easter in person and together again as the pandemic eases. However, they acknowledge that this day may be difficult for those who have lost loved ones or are living in challenging circumstances. They pray for peace, freedom, and dignity for all people. Looking to the future, they hope to share a common hope, love, and compassion. They send their wishes of hope, health, joy, and peace to the readers, and ask God's blessings upon them.